file=AI & Agents/meta/logical/book-requirements.md · h=name: meta-logical-book-requirements\ntype: logical\nstatus: built — 1 dedicated script + inherits from Shared OS (2026-07-15)\nassigned_agent: meta (AI & Agents / Fleet Orchestrator — department leader)\ndate_added: 2026-07-10\ndate_filled: 2026-07-15\n · p:=All logical scripts live in `Shared OS/logical/` (§13.5). Meta owns 1 dedicated script for fleet measurement and inherits cross-agent scripts. This file is the only file in this folder.\n · tb=\| # \| Script \| Source Book 1 \| Book 1 URL \| Source Book 2 \| Book 2 URL \| Route \| · tb=\|---\|--------\|--------------\|------------\|---------------\|------------\|-------\| · tb=\| 1 \| `fleet_measurement.py` \| DeMarco, *Controlling Software Projects* (Yourdon Press, 1982) \| [archive.org](https://archive.org/details/controllingsoftw0000dema) — FREE \| CETIC/Fenton & Pfleeger, *Software Metrics Overview* (GQM framework) \| [cetic.be](https://www.cetic.be/IMG/pdf/Software_Metrics_Overview.pdf) — FREE \| B/C \| · tb=\| Script \| Source Book \| Book URL \| Why Meta Needs It \| · tb=\|--------\|------------\|----------\|---------------------\| · tb=\| `signal_detection.py` \| OpenStax, *Introductory Business Statistics 2e* (2023) \| [openstax.org](https://openstax.org/details/books/introductory-business-statistics-2e) — FREE \| Statistical significance for fleet health trends \| · tb=\| `decision_analysis.py` \| Clemen & Reilly (2012) \| [archive.org](https://archive.org/details/makingharddecisi0000clem_u9f9) \| MAUT for promotion decisions \| · tb=\| `planning_fallacy.py` \| Kahneman (2011) \| [archive.org](https://archive.org/) \| Calibration for staffing/readiness projections \| · tb=\| Previously Flagged (0.6) \| Status \| Script \| · tb=\|--------------------------\|--------\|--------\| · tb=\| Fleet over/under-staffed quantitative criteria \| ✅ Cleared \| `fleet_measurement.py` (fleet_health_score — cost/schedule/quality/readiness composite) \| · tb=\| Standards-effectiveness measurement \| ✅ Cleared \| `fleet_measurement.py` (standards_effectiveness — pre/post violation rates with effect size) \| · tb=\| Promotion thresholds beyond gauge's operational metrics \| ✅ Cleared \| `fleet_measurement.py` (promotion_readiness — 5-gate model per DeMarco Ch.6-8) \| · sm:=- **fleet-orchestration** → imports `fleet_measurement.py` (fleet_health_score, standards_effectiveness)\n- **promotion-gate** → imports `fleet_measurement.py` (promotion_readiness)\n- **standards-governance** → imports `fleet_measurement.py` (standards_effectiveness)\n